From: Bo-Cun Chen <bc-bocun.chen@mediatek.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Sep 2025 12:56:11 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: mtk_ppe: fix typo for enabling MIB cache

The MIB cache enable was writing MTK_PPE_MIB_CFG_RD_CLR instead of
MTK_PPE_MIB_CACHE_CTL_EN, which meant the MIB cache was never actually
enabled. This can degrade PPE performance when per-flow accounting is
active.

Signed-off-by: Bo-Cun Chen <bc-bocun.chen@mediatek.com>
[dpawlik: ported from mtk-openwrt-feeds 25.12 999-ppe-10]
Signed-off-by: Daniel Pawlik <dpawlik@redhat.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_ppe.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_ppe.c
@@ -1122,7 +1122,7 @@ void mtk_ppe_start(struct mtk_ppe *ppe)
 		ppe_m32(ppe, MTK_PPE_MIB_CFG, MTK_PPE_MIB_CFG_RD_CLR,
 			MTK_PPE_MIB_CFG_RD_CLR);
 		ppe_m32(ppe, MTK_PPE_MIB_CACHE_CTL, MTK_PPE_MIB_CACHE_CTL_EN,
-			MTK_PPE_MIB_CFG_RD_CLR);
+			MTK_PPE_MIB_CACHE_CTL_EN);
 	}
 }
 
